english:
  title: 'Beacon Fire at Gyeongwon: Written in Exile'
  author: Hong Gwi-dal
  language: eng
  text: |-
    As the sun tilts westward at the frontier, the evening beacon rises.
    At this hour, the palace bells toll in the gathering dusk.
    I lament that my body is less fortunate than that beacon fire—
    I cannot fly to the summit of the mountain beyond the southern tower.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The beacon fire serves as a metaphor for the poet's longing for freedom and swift communication—the beacon can travel where the exiled poet cannot.
  - key: ''
    value: The poem was composed during the author's exile, a period of political disgrace in traditional Korean society.
